(987, 1, '2013-02-12 16:08:27', '2013-02-12 15:08:27', 'Hello dear gamers, streamers or really anyone who happens to read this!\r\n\r\nWe here at Gamers Live (a division of hostse.net) are pleased to announce a brand new service, called Gamers live!\r\nAnd what is Gamers Live you might ask, well its brand new live streaming platform for gamers.\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;">Our plans are to give a free service where users can stream there content to. Ad revenue will then be generated and uses who choose to partner up with us, are able to earn a minimum of 80 % of the total ad revenue generated by their stream and channel page. In some cases where a big amount of the revenue is planned to go to charity, we plan on giving up to 100 % of the ad revenue directly to that charity.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;">How is this possible you might then ask.\r\nWell within the last </span>couple<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;"> of years hostse has created a good networks of servers which we are taking in use for this project. And as we go and more users hopefully use our service, we will start being </span>independent<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;"> from hostse and might even generate profit.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;">Now many of you might wonder how our website is going to look like, well its going to be clean and simply but still with easy and fast navigation for users. Here is a small peek of what is still a work in progress:</span>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://gamers-live.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/screen_1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1020" alt="screen_1" src="http://gamers-live.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/screen_1-1024x630.png" width="1024" height="630" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span><span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;">As you can see we have aimed for a minimalist </span>approach<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;"> to the </span>design<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;"> of the front page, but still give plenty of navigation </span></span>possibilities. We feel like that user should be able to quick and with easy find the content they like. But also users who might not know what to watch will with easy gain new interests by our featured streams.\r\n\r\nFeatured streams are not necessarily popular streams but can be planned events or really anything we as moderators find interesting. Also you do not need to be a partner to get featured, you can be someone who have just signed up, and are planning to do a charity Star Craft 2 tournament, with a English commentator. Really there are no restrictions for getting featured other then it has to be English commentary and interesting.\r\n\r\nAnother big part of the design of each users channels is the ability to customize it. For normal users this will meaning changing background pictures, stream offline pictures, channel title + alot of information tabs about the stream, streamer and additional information.\r\n\r\nPartnered streamers will have the ability to create custom html pages with custom design (yes fully custom) something like the following:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://gamers-live.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/channel_test_1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1017" alt="channel_test_1" src="http://gamers-live.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/channel_test_1-1024x507.png" width="1024" height="507" /></a>\r\n\r\nAlthough there are some limitations for partnered streamers custom design of the pages, like have has to use our ads (and cant use your own, so you are not able to sell ads space on the page, although in custom cases we will allow this. An example would be: if you have a sponsor and you would like a banner to link to their product it can be allowed in special cases.)\r\n<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;">and you have to use the Gamers Live header and footer, everything in the middle are up to you. In some cases we will even allow PHP and JavaScript so you can poll and display data (maybe forum posts / news like in the example above) on your channel page. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;">As stated earlier this is </span>although<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;"> only for partnered users, but we are planning of an </span>implementation<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;"> to free users </span>as well<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;">. </span>Although<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;"> this is out far in the future.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;">So how do you then become partner? Well it is rather simple. There are 3 cases of how you can become a partner:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>You have a YouTube channel with more then 25.000 subscribers and your average video has been viewed more then 2.500 times</li>\r\n	<li>You are already live streaming on another platform (can also be here on gamers live), you live stream has more then an average of 100 viewers.</li>\r\n	<li>You are an event or streamer who will give all the revenue generated by ads to charity (there are no minimum requirements here, it will be a case to case decision.)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">Thats it, no funny business here.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;"> </span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">For "normal" users we will at start of beta also support some costum desing on our defualt channel page:</span></div>\r\n<div><a href="http://gamers-live.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/screen_defualt.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1018" alt="screen_defualt" src="http://gamers-live.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/screen_defualt.png" width="805" height="749" /></a></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;"> </span></div>\r\n<div><span><span style="line-height: normal;">Here users will be able to edit the header background img, the offline image and their avatar which is shown in search results. Of cause you will also be able to edit the stream title, info blocks etc. </span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;"> </span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">Well that was all for now, should you have any questions then please comment here or on our zendeks support panel which will function as our customer support panel. </span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;"> </span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">Best Regards,</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">Christoffer Mikkelsen</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">CEO of Gamers Live</span></div>', 'GAMERS LIVE Announcement', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fdsafdsaf', '', '', '2013-02-21 15:23:12', '2013-02-21 14:23:12', '', 0, 'http://gamers-live.net/blog/?p=987', 0, 'post', '', 1),
