thing in the middle are up to you. In some cases we will even allow PHP and JavaScript so you can poll and display data (maybe forum posts / news like in the example above) on your channel page. Also donation addons for kick starter or just a simple paypal donation button are allowed.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;">As stated earlier this is </span>although<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;"> only for partnered users, but we are planning of an </span>implementation<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;"> to free users </span>as well<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;">. </span>Although<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;"> this is out far in the future.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.45em;">So how do you then become partner? Well it is rather simple. There are 3 cases of how you can become a partner:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>You have a YouTube channel with more then 25.000 subscribers and your average video has been viewed more then 2.500 times</li>\r\n	<li>You are already live streaming on another platform (can also be here on gamers live), you live stream has more then an average of 100 viewers.</li>\r\n	<li>You are an event or streamer who will give all the revenue generated by ads to charity (there are no minimum requirements here, it will be a case to case decision.)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">Thats it, no funny business here.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;"> </span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">For "normal" users we will at start of beta also support some costum desing on our defualt channel page:</span></div>\r\n<div><a href="http://gamers-live.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/screen_defualt.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1018" alt="screen_defualt" src="http://gamers-live.net/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/screen_defualt.png" width="805" height="749" /></a></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;"> </span></div>\r\n<div><span><span style="line-height: normal;">Here users will be able to edit the header background img, the offline image and their avatar which is shown in search results. Of cause you will also be able to edit the stream title, info blocks etc. </span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;"> </span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">Well that was all for now, should you have any questions then please comment here on our zendeks support panel which will functions as our customer support panel and news announcements (news announcements might change to our blog when our page is online but for now its here, costumer support will always be on this panel). </span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">If you want to contact us directly then you can send your concerns to admin@gamers-live.net or comments on this article.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;"> </span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">Best Regards,</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">Christoffer Mikkelsen</span></div>\r\n<div><span style="line-height: normal;">CEO of Gamers Live</span></div>', 'GAMERS LIVE Announcement', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '987-revision-12', '', '', '2013-02-12 17:08:45', '2013-02-12 16:08:45', '', 987, 'http://gamers-live.net/blog/1029', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
